\ A load-time error carries a file:line prefix: the loader knows the file, and
\ the line is the newline count to the failing token. Caught here with try-catch
\ so the located :message shows; an uncaught one prints the same at the REPL.

\ compile error on line 3
"3 4 + drop
5 6 * drop
bogus drop
" "/tmp/lf141a.h2o" write-file
[: "/tmp/lf141a.h2o" load :] [: :message @ . cr :] try-catch   \ ...lf141a.h2o:3: unknown word: bogus

\ a runtime fault in top-level code is located at the triggering line
"1 2 + drop
3 0 /
" "/tmp/lf141b.h2o" write-file
[: "/tmp/lf141b.h2o" load :] [: :message @ . cr :] try-catch   \ ...lf141b.h2o:2: division by zero

\ unterminated definition -> located at the end-of-file line
": f 1 2 +
" "/tmp/lf141c.h2o" write-file
[: "/tmp/lf141c.h2o" load :] [: :message @ . cr :] try-catch   \ ...lf141c.h2o:2: unterminated definition

\ nested load: the error locates to the innermost file, not the outer one
"oops drop
" "/tmp/lf141inner.h2o" write-file
"1 drop
""/tmp/lf141inner.h2o"" load
" "/tmp/lf141outer.h2o" write-file
[: "/tmp/lf141outer.h2o" load :] [: :message @ . cr :] try-catch   \ ...lf141inner.h2o:1: unknown word: oops
bye
